WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Former Artistic Director of National Opera House ballet troupe is back to Ukraine

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
World-famous Ukrainian ballet dancer, Denis Matvienko

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:12.000
is preparing to present his new project

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.000
It will be a ballet performance, based on “The Great Gatsby” novel

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.000
In Kiev Matvienko is looking for cast of the future ballet

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:22.000
Among the candidates there are dancers from Donetsk and ballet stars from Kiev opera

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:25.000
Our reporter, Olga Symak, has seen the first fragment of the upcoming premiere

00:00:26.500 --> 00:00:28.500

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:30.000

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.000
More than 50 dancers are rushing to THE GREAT GATSBY ballet audition

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:39.000
being thoroughly assessed by world-renowned Ukrainian dancer, Denis Matvienko

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:44.000
and famous American choreographer, founder of Complexions Contemporary Ballet, Dwight Rhoden

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.000
“I’m seeking original dancers. I have no stereotypes or any limitations”

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
“We need high-skilled techniques and charisma. They must have it all”

00:00:57.000 --> 00:00:59.000
Among the candidates there are students as well as experienced dancers. 

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Viktor Ishchuk has got a number of solo parts

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:08.000
even a 31-year old soloist of National Opera House of Ukraine is looking for new challenges

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
It’s a great challenge, opportunity and prospect

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Her ballet career has been cut off by war in the East

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:19.000
After 7 years of studying in Belarus Lisa is back to her native Donetsk

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:24.000
In “Donbass Opera Theatre” she was preparing for her first solo part in “Le Bayadere”

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
From the beginning of ATO, “Donbass Opera Theatre” has preliminary stopped its activity

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:31.000
She’s just arrived in Kiev in the morning by the train from Donetsk

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:34.500
“I came here right from the railway station with my luggage

00:01:34.500 --> 00:01:40.000
Due to the situation in Donetsk, there is a need to find something new, especially when there is an opportunity to join such an interesting project 

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:45.000
I’ve read the book, watched the film many times, so now my dreams are coming true”

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:50.000
“Now you’ll see the part of choreography from THE GREAT GATSBY ballet in order to feel this style”

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:55.000
52-year old American choreographer Dwight Rhoden is named as “one of the most sought out choreographers of the day”

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:58.000
His dancers should stand at points firmly

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:02.500
he also exceeds the frames of classical ballet by adding elements of street dance

00:02:02.500 --> 00:02:08.000
In THE GREAT GATSBY ballet, as he confesses, he will allow himself to implement a share of frivolity

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
“Our story is based on the famous novel. The plot is taken from there. 

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:15.500
It will be contemporary ballet with classical base

00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:19.000
The choreography will contain the style of 20-s

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:22.000
It will be a real explosive mix of different techniques and styles”

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:25.000
Music is composed by Konstantin Meladze

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:28.000
The leading part of Jay Gatsby will be performed by Denis Matvienko

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
Premiere performances in Kiev are scheduled in October

